    "coverageEstimate": "Strong coverage of OBC priories, IZAUK dojos, WCF Chan groups, StoneWater groups, the two Rinzai/Sanbo houses, Kwan Um London, and the Plum Village UK in-person sangha network. Plum Village figures dominate the count; smaller informal sitting groups, individual dharma-successor home dojos, and Channel Islands sanghas are partially included. Soto-shu Europe directory and obcon.org/temples/ both returned 403/404 at fetch time, but list was reconstructed from tbpriory.org.uk's OBC links page.",
    "knownGaps": [
      "Plum Village UK address detail: in-person groups list city/region but rarely give street addresses on the public directory; URLs default to plumvillage.uk find-a-group entries",
      "Some StoneWater satellites (Chesterfield) lack public URLs",
      "White Plum independents beyond StoneWater + Wholehearted Zen are sparse — Keizan Roshi listed as Europe rep but standalone UK sitting groups not separately published",
      "Obaku presence in UK appears negligible; no current standalone Obaku temple identified",
      "Sotoshu (sotozen.com) UK temple page was 404 on collection day; relied on OBC + IZAUK + StoneWater for Soto coverage",
      "Channel Islands (Guernsey, Jersey) included under Plum Village though technically Crown Dependencies, not UK constituent countries"
    ]
